docs.text:
PyMapManager is a Python package to analyze time-series image stacks.


PyMapManager opens annotations created with the Igor Pro version of 
Map Manager
. Allowing additional analysis to easily be performed.


There are three components to PyMapManager:




Python Package


Server


Desktop application




PyMapManager Python package


See the 
/examples
 folder in the main GitHub repository for example Python code to easily perform additional analysis. Please also see the 
API Documentation
.


PyMapManager server


The PyMapManager server allows web-based browsing of annotations and stacks. See 
server documentation
 for additional information.


Browsing annotations




Browsing annotations in time series stacks






PyMapManager deskop application


The Qt version of PyMapManager is a desktop application. See 
github repository
.
